caption: Great takeout during the pandemic. Fish is so fresh, the rolls, nigiri, chirashi all delicious. Can't wait to sit at the sushi bar when things fully reopen. 🍣🍣

This is my favorite sushi place in the city! They serve consistently delicious sushi for an extremely reasonable price. And, they are part of the neighborhood. The owner/sushi chef waves every time we go by!
Unbelievable sushi, and very reasonably priced. I’m blown away.
You will not be disappointed by the quality of the sushi or really anything. Superb freshness and definitely worth it

Wow. This place impressed us. Fantastic sushi that doesn't break the bank. Had to order take out due to the shutdown and the sushi was fresh, well packaged, and just delicious. Ordered the omakase and added a roll and some other items. …

Came here on a Friday night and it was packed! They don't take reservations (on Fridays at least) so I'd recommend putting your name down and then going to shop around at Homegoods or Nordstrom Rack in the same complex or be prepared to wait. You'll get a text when your table is ready.
Really good sushi, they don’t open until 6p for dinner wish they opened earlier. Really good fresh fish.

This is one of our favorite neighborhood restaurants. They are offering takeout while shelter-in-place is in effect. I ordered 4 rolls and 2 appetizers over the phone and picked them up in 20 minutes. The fresh sushi was delicious!
Our favorite place.  Service is great, the foot is outstanding. These are tough times for these small restaurant owners.  They offer take out, let’s help them out.

A quaint establishment with a classic feel. Extremely friendly service. Rolls are simple and the fish smells and tastes fresh.

We go to Wayo all the time. Short menu but always fresh and well made. Small restaurant with just one sushi chef (the owner) so wait can be long some times...if you are patient (or have a book / good company) it is with the wait.
excelent sushi place! meal is made in front of you. all is fresh and very tasty!
Awesome fresh sushi and quick service. Very reasonable prices and service is amazing. Highly recommend for a low key dinner w a few friends. Try the scallop nigri...was out of this world.

Good spot, three dollar signs not two though. Prices are good but rolls are small. Ate 40 of food in about 45 seconds. Hot tea out of this world, they add Bailey (I think) to it to give it this earthy taste, complements the saltines of the soy sauce perfectly.
Best low key sushi in San Francisco. A true Tokyo experience. This is the gem I promised to tell no one about! The fish quality is what keeps me coming back.

What a gem.  A little corner sushi place where everything is very well done.  The couple that run the place really care and were super attentive.  The lunch specials are a bit pricy, but well worth it.

This place is great...Fairly simple menu with emphasis towards nigiri/sashimi.. quality fresh ingredients for an affordable price. One thing to note, Get there when it opens, because after a few tables roll in it slows the service down a bit with it being him and one lady only.
Quality authentic Japanese food. Sushi was great, and the service was spectacular.
This place is awesome!  The owners are actually Japanese and their sushi is some of the best I've ever had in The City.  I highly recommend getting your sushi fix here!

This has always been my favorite sushi spot in the whole city which i can come any time. Casual and friendly. Fish are great and the rice is what to come for, always freshly made. Even the fake crabs feel “real” here. Plus point for a cute and clean toilet in the neighborhood.

I love this place for their salmon.  succulent, soft, and savory.  If you don't like salmon, I would still recommend giving this place a try, maybe it'll change your thoughts on it.  They also have a seasonal menu near the door as well.
Very good flavors.  Attention to detail.
The guy making the sushi here really knows his stuff. Good price, AMAZING quality. I'll be coming here again for sure.

excellent Saba nigiri! the uni was also very delicious! Overall, great sushi and a great experience at this place. The restaurant has only two people working but they are both really nice and give great service. Highly recommend!

One of my favorite sushi restaurants. Extremely low key, only two staff (chef and waitress), easy to get a seat and GREAT sushi. Small little place with Jazz lightly playing in the background. About 15 counter seats and four tables. Excessively no-pretentious and generally reasonable.
I'm a big fan of the sushi here.  The atmosphere is very low-key, though, and the place is so small that the odds are low of getting seated on the weekend.  Thus, it's best as a neighborhood spot.

Hidden sushi gem on Van Ness! We sat at the bar and realized that there was only one sushi maker doing all of the rolls, but that made the experience so much more intimate and special. We ordered appetizers while we waited for our sushi and …

I love this place! I came to San Francisco on vacation and looked up sushi and this is where I landed. The sushi was fresh, service was friendly.  Came with my sister and we had time to talk and enjoy our food. Try the Dragon roll and the …
Sushi is my favorite food, and I've tried many places in the bay. This place topped my favorite by far. Great experience, nice couple, and delicious sushi!

I was not expecting the freshness of the sashimi for a place as cheap as this was.  For two people, we got five rolls and two sashimi plates and we paid 60 dollars after tax and tip.  There is one guy that does everything.  He the waiter, chef, bus boy, and dishwasher.  If it's crowded, the food comes out slowly, so get there early.

Wayo is my go to sushi spot! The place itself is small and generic but the sushi here is fantastic. The fish is fresh and well presented and the service is always good. There's just one sushi chef and one assistant so it can take a little time, but it's worth the wait if you're not in a rush.

Excellent no-frills sushi spot. Just one sushi chef and one additional staff member so don't go if you're in a rush.
Tiny delicious little hole in the wall. I recommend sitting at the bar and ordering brown rice with your rolls - yum!

Service can be slow going (it's a two person operation) but the fish is fresh and the sushi authentic. A nice place to sit at the counter and unwind. My favorites are hotate (scallop) and saba (mackerel) nigiri and the snow leopard roll (seared yellowtail with ponzu sauce).

If your looking for fancy rolls with even fancier names, this is not the place for you.  If you want very fresh traditional sushi, this is your place!  Very friendly service, and fresh fish make this place a must try.

I had my first date with my wife there in 1991 and continued eating there until 1994. Went back in 2004 and the place was amazing still. Best sushi ever. Sent friends there in jibe 2011 and they were very impressed with the quality and prices. The owner is the chef and Japan town is around the corner. Freshest sushi.
